# M3U Lineup Rules

Use these rules whenever you work on `official.m3u` or any other IPTV playlist in this repo.

## Editorial policy

- Treat the playlist like a provider lineup, not a dump of sources.
- Prioritize Latin American channels over non-priority markets.
- Keep Brazil and other non-priority regions behind the main LATAM block unless a source is uniquely necessary.
- Prefer `1080p` versions first.
- Keep ordering aligned with real IPTV providers: national, kids, movies, series, sports, news, music, documentaries, and then the rest.

## Sorting behavior

- Group all national channels together.
- Keep channel families together when the same channel appears in multiple qualities or regions.
- Put the best and most stable source first.
- Leave lower-quality or backup streams below the primary stream.
- Do not sort alphabetically unless the user asks for it.

## M3U hygiene

- Preserve `#EXTM3U`, `#EXTINF`, `tvg-id`, `tvg-name`, `tvg-logo`, `group-title`, `user-agent`, and `#EXTVLCOPT`.
- Do not invent metadata.
- Keep the file valid for common IPTV players.
